@@TJvRollOut
<TITLEIMG TJvRollOut>
#JVCLInfo
<GROUP JVCL.PanelsBevelsAndGroups.Panels>
<FLAG Component>
Summary
  A control that acts like a pane but can also alter its height or width to predefined values.
Description
  Use a TJvRollOut when screen real-estate is at a premium or if the form contains a multitude of
  controls that can be logically grouped and where each group doesn't have to be visible at the same
  time as other groups. The rollout also has a button that is used at runtime to expand and collapse
  the control.
  
  To use a TJvRollOut, drop it on a form and:
  
  * Set Placement to specify in what direction the control expands and collapses and where the button
    is located.
  * Set Collapsed to true and adjust the rollout's width and height to define its collapsed size.
  * Set Collapsed to false and adjust the rollout's width and height to define its expanded size.
  * When Collapsed is false, drop other visual controls on the surface of the rollout. These controls
    will only be visible while the rollout is expanded.

